      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "MILES, Wash, Nov. 29.-About\n$50 Indians have assembled here\nat the request Of Inspector General\nJames Mclaughlin of the interior\ndepartment to discuss the opening\nOf the south half of the Colville\nreservation to white people. If the\nreservation is opened for settle\nment the land will be allotted to\nthe Indians with a money payment\nOf $1,500,000. The meeting at\nMiles Told Fort Spokane) means\nthe keeping or the opening Of one\nof the finest tracts of land in the\nwest."
    }
  ]
